>[Question]
>It is no doubt a basic question however I would be interested to know 
>how the equation for cross sectional area of  a cylindrical (wire) 
>specimen is determined [ pi x diam^2] / 4
>
>[Difficulty]
>unsure why it diam^2 
>
>[Thoughts]
>assumed that area of circle was used....

Hello Joel,

The area of a circle of RADIUS r is pi*r^2.  Because the diameter d is 2r, that is d=2r, we 
see that in terms of diameter the area is

pi*r^2 = pi*(d/2)^2 = pi*d^2/4


